    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I enjoyed ''On Some Corporate Internet Sites, It's Not All Business'' (Sept. 7), and must offer my favorite: www.krispykreme.com.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I enjoyed ''On Some Corporate Internet Sites, It's Not All Business'' (Sept. 7), and must offer my favorite: www.krispykreme.com.</p>
        <p>The real fun on Krispy Kreme's site comes when you click on the doughnut icon marked Taste and press the button that leads to the ''instructions'' on making their doughnuts. From the detailed directions (''get a really big truck'') to the out-and-out corporate secrets (where do they get the holes for the doughnuts?), it is a pleasure to read and reassures one that some part of corporate America retains a sense of humor.</p>
        <p>NAOMI SIEGEL  Pittsburgh</p>
      </block>
